<Class name="CM_UnitTestAgent" id="2ca2d309-a29f-48b5-a128-b40572b9e014">
    <superclass name="CM_Agent"/>
    <transient/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>NOTE
====

This class is here to support Unit testing of the Web Services messages.
Before adding a method here, read the instructions in the method "webServiceCall"
on the class "UT_DSL" in the schema "JMTUnitTest".
The method you add will then need to be re-implemented in the class "WS_UnitTestAgent"
in "WebServicesSchema".
The method you add here will be referenced from your unit test in "JMTUnitTest""
and its name passed to the method "webServiceCall" on the class "UT_DSL" in the
schema "JMTUnitTest".

All this means that eventhough we are using a grubby "sendMsg" to call the
re-implemented version on the subclass "WS_UnitTest" in "WebServicesSchema",
we will still have some references to tie it all together for the hapless developer
that may have to maintain this code in the future. </text>
    <DbClassMap file="WebTest"/>
    <ImplicitInverseRef name="myTerminal" id="9a50b492-d992-45de-8275-24136f83ec8b">
